Rating: 4
This pie is EXCEPTIONAL. I loved it! Perfect summer pie! That said, this crust is not for the faint of heart, it becomes extraordinarily soft the second it hits air making it difficult to roll out and form the lattice. What I did: I always roll my crusts between waxed paper or parchment to keep oils off it. I rolled out the first half, popped it in the freezer, rolled the second, froze, fitted bottom into dish, back in freezer, sliced up strips, refroze, wove them on waxed paper, back into freezer, filled bottom with fruit and then CAREFULLY transfered lattice onto pie (by gently folding it in half- waxed against waxed- and laying one half on top and slowly folding the rest over the fruit) and then trimmed and crimped edges. I think anyone wanting to make this should know what they are getting into. If this seems scary-- use a crust you know is easy to work with. After all the work the crust was insanely flakey, flavorful (could have used a pinch more salt, though). The middle was delish-- I halved the cinnamon (which I believe was the better move since you can sort of tell its there but doesn't detract from the strawbs or the rubarb). And I used a heaping 1/4 c cornstarch. I love Strawberry Rhubarb anything and this will be the pie I make from here on out!

