A good pie recipe that I built upon with a tip I got from cooking.com. ;-) Instead of flour or cornstarch, I used uncooked tapioca as the thickening agent. I also used fresh strawberries rather than frozen, which are especially good in the summer and readily available year round. This pie came out sweet but not overly so, perfect with whipped cream or ice cream.

